(198, 4, '2021-10-24 16:28:31', '2021-10-24 14:28:31', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>TEST : </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Computer programming</strong>&nbsp;is the process of designing and building an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Executable\">executable</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_program\">computer program</a>&nbsp;to accomplish a specific&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computing\">computing</a>&nbsp;result or to perform a specific task. Programming involves tasks such as: analysis, generating&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algorithm\">algorithms</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Profiling_(computer_programming)\">profiling</a>&nbsp;algorithms\' accuracy and resource consumption, and the implementation of algorithms in a chosen&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Programming_language\">programming language</a>&nbsp;(commonly referred to as&nbsp;<strong>coding</strong>).<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_programming#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup><sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_programming#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Source_code\">source code</a>&nbsp;of a program is written in one or more languages that are intelligible to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Programmer\">programmers</a>, rather than&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_code\">machine code</a>, which is directly executed by the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_processing_unit\">central processing unit</a>. The purpose of programming is to find a sequence of instructions that will automate the performance of a task (which can be as complex as an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operating_system\">operating system</a>) on a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer\">computer</a>, often for solving a given problem. Proficient programming thus often requires expertise in several different subjects, including knowledge of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Domain_(software_engineering)\">application domain</a>, specialized algorithms, and formal&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logic\">logic</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tasks accompanying and related to programming include:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_testing\">testing</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Debugging\">debugging</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Source_code\">source code</a>&nbsp;maintenance, implementation of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Build_automation\">build systems</a>, and management of derived&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artifact_(software_development)\">artifacts</a>, such as the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_code\">machine code</a>&nbsp;of computer programs. These might be considered part of the programming process, but often the term&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_development\">software development</a></em>&nbsp;is used for this larger process with the term&nbsp;<em>programming</em>,&nbsp;<em>implementation</em>, or&nbsp;<em>coding</em>&nbsp;reserved for the actual writing of code.&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_engineering\">Software engineering</a></em>&nbsp;combines&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Engineering\">engineering</a>&nbsp;techniques with software development practices.&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reverse_engineering\">Reverse engineering</a></em>&nbsp;is a related process used by designers, analysts and programmers to understand and re-create/re-implement.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_programming#cite_note-Eilam-3\">[3]</a></sup></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'ACCUEIL', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-10-24 16:28:31', '2021-10-24 14:28:31', '', 5, 'http://localhost/projetgroupe/?p=198', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(223, 4, '2021-10-24 17:57:18', '2021-10-24 15:57:18', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>La force du CFA INSTA, est de s’être spécialisé depuis sa création, dans l’accompagnement des étudiant(e)s et la prise en compte de chaque situation et motivation pour leur offrir un vrai tremplin pour leur projet d’avenir professionnel.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>En effet, notre but est de permettre aux étudiant(e)s d’acquérir à la fois un diplôme reconnu sur le marché de l’emploi, mais également une expérience professionnelle en adéquation avec ce diplôme grâce à l’alternance et au stage pour le BTS SIO en initiale. Nous avons également comme valeur d’aider les personnes en rupture ou en échec scolaire, de se réinserer dans le milieu du travail à travers nos titres professionnels et les passerelles universitaires. Nous proposons également des stages d’initiations aux futur(e)s étudiant(e)s en BTS SIO et en BTS CG. Notre équipe compte plus de 100 intervenants et experts d’origine universitaire et professionnelle. Nos intervenants se sont distingués sur le plan international à travers leurs interventions professionnelles auprès des entreprises et leurs différentes publications sur différents thèmes (technique, management, RH, etc.). Enfin, nous plaçons au cœur de notre pédagogie la notion de projet, chaque séquence de formation étant couronnée par une soutenance à laquelle sont associés les tuteurs et maîtres d’apprentissage pour les étudiant(e)s en alternance, ce qui permet de renforcer les liens avec l’environnement professionnel de nos stagiaires et de mesurer constamment la pertinence de nos formations afin qu’elles restent adaptées au marché.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'L\'ÉCOLE', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-10-24 17:57:18', '2021-10-24 15:57:18', '', 36, 'http://localhost/projetgroupe/?p=223', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
